                     <interp inst="t18230910-215-person1962" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 29th of August, about the middle of the day, I saw the prisoner by my father's door with two or three more. I was coming to the door, and saw them looking at the shoes which hung at the doorpost - they took them down, and hung them up again, and then I went away.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-215-person1963">
                  ISSAC 
                  CLARK
               <interp inst="t18230910-215-person1963" type="surname" value="CLARK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-215-person1963" type="given" value="ISSAC"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-215-person1963" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live opposite Ward, at <placeName id="t18230910-215-crimeloc1177">Highgate</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-215-crimeloc1177" type="placeName" value="Highgate"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-215-crimeloc1177" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-215-off1175 t18230910-215-crimeloc1177"></join>. On the 29th of August, about two o'clock, I saw four boys at his door; the prisoner was one of them. I did not see him take the boots; my son said they were stolen. I saw the prisoner with something bulky in his apron; I went over to Ward's, and saw them crossing the road, and took hold of one of the others - the prisoner then ran up a little passage, and came out without the bulk - I went to him and asked what he had done with the shoes - I found them in the passage, behind the door, where he went up.</p>
